Your room key will allow you into the gym, the steam room/sauna part of the spa and the Spa Atrium.  You can lounge or get work done in the lobby, or conference rooms too!
properties.interaction: We are a full service property with 24 hour staff. If you have any questions or requests we are here to help at any time.  We also have 24 hour security and door staff so you can feel safe in your home away from home.
properties.house_rules: The OUT is a completely non-smoking property. Any guests who are smoking on property will be charged a penalty fee.  Check in is any time after 4pm and check out is at 11am.  Guests must be 18 years or older to check in with a valid for of ID.  Housekeeping service is provided every three days.  You may request toiletries and towels at any time during your stay. We are a dog/cat friendly property and require a 150 non-refundable cleaning fee in the event that you are accompanied by a furry friend.

properties.neighborhood_overview: Once a notoriously overcrowded and unsanitary slum, the Lower East Side is now one of Manhattan’s most fashionable neighborhoods. Most of the bargain-clothing stores and pickle vendors have given way to indie boutiques and scenery eateries, though there are a few cherished survivors of the former Jewish stronghold, including venerable smoked-fish purveyors Russ & Daughters and pastrami legend Katz’s Delicatessen. The Tenement Museum keeps the neighborhood’s history alive in a series of restored apartments visited via themed guided tours, but most of the area’s cultural draws are contemporary: The arrival of the New Museum on the Bowery several years ago drew numerous art galleries to the LES (TIME OUT Magazine).

properties.host_about:
I am of Scottish descent, originally born in New York city in 1984.  I love New York City and I really love being in the Lower East Side.  I've lived in the West Village, East Village, Union Square, Tribeca, and now The Lower East Side.  One of the last neighborhoods in New York City to go through gentrification, I still feel as though it is a beautiful melting pot of art, culture and culinary magic.  It truly a "neighborhood".  I hope if you stay in the LES, I hope you explore and come to feel the same way.

I work quite a lot and have to travel quite a bit but I do love it.  My favorite places to be are the highlands of Scotland, Costa Rica, and pretty much haven't seen a beach I didnt like:)  

Life motto: "Smooth seas don't make skillful sailor"

properties.host_about:
I am an addicted travel junkie. You can always hear me talking to my friends raving about travel opportunities and places. 

Can't live without: Travel, Family, Simple life, fun experiences 

Travel!!: I am working on traveling everywhere, but right now my fav destinations would be Thailand for it's unique cultural experiences, tasty cuisine, and interesting outdoor activities to take part in! Bali is also a close second with its chill atmosphere and great places to meditate, do yoga, surf, and just hang out with friendly locals! 

Books: I love those books that are unconventional. I love to listen to other people's opinions and formulate my own on all kinds of topics, particularly living styles. Think and Grow Rich is on my kindle right now. 

Shows: Anthony Bordain! ( get to see all the cool foods around the world I can eat), House Hunters International (get to see all the cool places around the world I can live in), Bizarre foods with Andrew Zimmerman ( get to experience unique food eating without having to eat them myself!), Friends (just because it's a classic), Modern Family (bc it's a modern take on comedy like Friends) anything cool 

Music: Anything that sounds cool to me, could be mainstream, could be indie, could be "hipster" 

Food: All kinds! But particularly on the healthier side of things, less red meat, more vegetation! 

I love to go to hostels and meet new people traveling like myself, share our experiences, and learn a thing or two. 

If I hosted, I would be so enthusiastic about showing guests around town and making them feel more like a friend than anything else. 

Life Motto: Being Unrealistic IS realistic.

properties.neighborhood_overview: There's no better place to experience the excitement of New York than Times Square. Surrounded by neon lights, giant billboards, Broadway theaters, electronic ticker tape and television studios, Times Square is truly the heart of Midtown. The TKTS Discount Booth (where theater tickets are sold at up to 50% off face value) is topped with a giant red staircase, open to visitors daily until 1am. Elsewhere in Times Square, the City has created several new pedestrian-only zones furnished with tables and chairs, perfect for people-watching. The neighborhood is central to Midtown West, located near the Theatre District and Broadway shows.
properties.transit: Located steps from Times Square and all major subway stations + walking distance to Port Authority bus terminal, Penn Station and Grand Central Station you'll enjoy living in the heart of the city!

Hi! My name is William. I am a 22 year old student in New York City. I am originally from New Jersey, but have lived in NYC for 3 years. I a Business student full time and manage my properties. I'm very excited to share my homes and apartments with you. Each one is quaint and unique, and have brought me much joy.

 
I am very much into Yoga, gardening, healthy living and meditation. I am a collector of abstract expressionist art. I enjoy traveling the world and meeting people from all over. I speak Spanish and German conversationally, so I can speak to you in those if you are a native speaker. 

My life motto is to enjoy life, smile, enjoy the beautiful world we live in and get to know yourself the best you can while trying to understand the ones around you. 

I am excited to share my homes with you! They are all special in their very own ways. Whether you are looking for a stay in an artsy, historic neighborhood in one the best cities in the world, a beautiful, peaceful stay off the great Lake Michigan, or a vacation home with a view of the ocean at my beach house in Long Beach Island, I am able to accommodate your travel wishes and plans. 

There is nothing like the sweet feeling of travel. 

Cheers and great travels!
William

properties.neighborhood_overview: This is without a doubt the best neighborhood in Manhattan. The streets are small which promotes a real community vibe. The apartment is just steps away from incredible bars, restaurants and shops. Hop across the street in the warmer months to browse the famed Hester Street Fair. Some neighborhood staples include Doughnut Plant, Kossar's Bialy and The Pickle Guys. North Dumpling is delicious and perfect for those traveling on a budget. These are ALL within 2 blocks of the apartment.  Across the street is a track with tennis, racquet and basketball courts. Each is available at a first come first serve basis, which is very rare and wonderful for NYC (most others require permits)! I have 2 tennis racquets and a basketball for your use, and you can purchase tennis balls at the bodega half a block down Essex on the corner of Hester street.

properties.host_about:
I'm a 36 year old female, living with her best friend (my Boxer, Oxford) in the East Village. I've been a New Yorker for life (at heart), but technically for 8 years now. I'm a graduate student in Columbia's MFA Film Program in Creative Producing. I am currently finishing up my degree, producing independent films, writing, working a coffee shop gig, doing lots of yoga, and loving my life!

I have a love affair with New York City and like to share that passion with my guests - tips, the "best of" advice, etc. Some of my other life pleasures are good coffee, sarcasm and dark humor, cooking, whiskey, the ocean/beach, late night city-walks with my dog, meditation and yoga, traveling, and staring at the moon.

Some favorites: Paris and the south of France, the films "Taxi Driver" and Baz Luhrman's "Romeo + Juliet," VEGGIES and good seafood, on the cuisine front, and MY DOG!!

Around the apartment, I'm a pretty private, introspective and quiet person. I generally like to keep to myself and value the space as my place where I can be alone and away from having to interact with the world. Outside, in the "world," I'm a mixed bag - a surefire extrovert, with introvert tendencies from time to time.

My life motto, if you will...the thought I try to keep in mind to keep me centered: the past is done, the future does not exist, the only thing that is REAL, is now.

properties.neighborhood_overview: Only steps to SoHo, the exotic China Town, the Village and Lower East Side! Walking beside the narrow, cobble-stoned streets beneath the fire escapes of turn-of-the-century tenements, you're tempted by the sights, sounds and smells of Italian cuisine and culture emanating from the restaurants surrounding you at every step. Here at Little Italy NYC, we're bringing it all to you! See our restaurant list and map to visit many of these restaurants at littleitalynyc com. Get an idea for the restaurant that's right for you and your family and friends. And when you arrive in Little Italy, you can say "you've been here before." Remember, Little Italy isn't just a San Gennaro Festival in September, it's year-round. You may not be able to win that stuffed animal, but you can still sure stuff yourself! A coal brick oven pizza...a hearty glass of Chianti...a zeppole...a cannoli...you'll find it all in New York City's Little Italy.

Only one of several condominium buildings located along the prime stretch of Central Park West’s Gold Coast, this residence is the perfect home away from home. Impeccably maintained with its mid-century modern furnishings and curated art collection, this distinctive two bedroom, three bathroom, study-den plus kitchen and accompanying breakfast room awaits the discerning visitor and offers the ultimate in sophisticated living.

A welcoming foyer gives way to a gracious layout – a 26 foot living/dining room area flanked by artwork by a renowned Chinese ink-brush artist, two sizeable bedrooms, a quiet retreat study/guestroom, and three full marble baths. The serene master bedroom is especially large and well portioned with an en-suite bath. Equally impressive, the windowed kitchen boasts Miele appliances, Dornbracht fixtures, a Subzero refrigerator and glass-front kitchen cabinets. The apartment also has a washer/dryer and many closets.

properties.neighborhood_overview: New York City has launched a thousand dreams and inspired millions; it’s yours to discover – and The OUT Hotel places the best of it at your doorstep. Located right in Hell’s Kitchen we’re just moments away from Times Square the Javits Center and countless other Midtown attractions that make your NYC vacation unforgettable. And while you could spend your entire visit within a one-mile radius of the hotel and never run out of things to do and see, we encourage you to travel a bit further afield while you’re here, and explore some of the other landmarks that define this incredible city.
properties.notes: Few areas of New York City have experienced as much of a rebirth in recent decades as Hell’s Kitchen. In the last 30 years, it’s established itself as one of the city’s most sought-after neighborhoods, thanks in part to the emergence of upscale apartment buildings and ambitious redevelopment projects. Hell’s Kitchen is also home to a thriving arts scene, and many aspiring actors live here. The OUT Hotel is ideally situated in Hell’s Kitchen, just a few moments from the area’s most captivating attractions. Step out of our door and explore!
properties.transit: Whether you’re in New York for work or for play, you won’t find a better place to call home than the OUT Hotel. Perfectly situated on 42nd Street in Hell’s Kitchen, steps from the Javits Center and Times Square, our hotel puts the best of Midtown Manhattan within your reach. If you have any questions for us, or would like to make a comment about a recent stay, don’t hesitate to get in touch.
properties.access: Our unparalleled location in the middle of Midtown Manhattan is perhaps one of our biggest perks, but it’s just the tip of the iceberg at our luxury NYC hotel. Relax in our gardens, break a sweat in the fitness center, or indulge in a massage at the spa, followed by a visit to the spectacular Spa Atrium. There’s an abundance of amenities at our luxury hotel, waiting to be enjoyed. Need anything during your stay? Our on-site concierge will be happy to help you.
properties.interaction: Our 24 hour front desk and concierge team is available to assist you during your stay.  Housekeeping service is provided every 3 days.

Your room key will allow you into the gym, the steam room/sauna part of the spa and the Spa Atrium.  You can lounge or get work done in the lobby, or conference rooms too!
properties.interaction: We are a full service property with 24 hour staff. If you have any questions or requests we are here to help at any time.  We also have 24 hour security and door staff so you can feel safe in your home away from home.

properties.neighborhood_overview: There's no better place to experience the excitement of New York than Times Square. Surrounded by neon lights, giant billboards, Broadway theaters, electronic ticker tape and television studios, Times Square is truly the heart of Midtown. The TKTS Discount Booth (where theater tickets are sold at up to 50% off face value) is topped with a giant red staircase, open to visitors daily until 1am. Elsewhere in Times Square, the City has created several new pedestrian-only zones furnished with tables and chairs, perfect for people-watching. The neighborhood is central to Midtown West, located near the Theatre District and Broadway shows.
properties.notes: The shared rooms are co-ed.  We take requests for all male or all female rooms seriously and will do what we can to accommodate those requests.  Unfortunately, we cannot guarantee all female or male roommates.

properties.host_about:
I'm a 36 year old female, living with her best friend (my Boxer, Oxford) in the East Village. I've been a New Yorker for life (at heart), but technically for 8 years now. I'm a graduate student in Columbia's MFA Film Program in Creative Producing. I am currently finishing up my degree, producing independent films, writing, working a coffee shop gig, doing lots of yoga, and loving my life!

I have a love affair with New York City and like to share that passion with my guests - tips, the "best of" advice, etc. Some of my other life pleasures are good coffee, sarcasm and dark humor, cooking, whiskey, the ocean/beach, late night city-walks with my dog, meditation and yoga, traveling, and staring at the moon.

Some favorites: Paris and the south of France, the films "Taxi Driver" and Baz Luhrman's "Romeo + Juliet," VEGGIES and good seafood, on the cuisine front, and MY DOG!!

Around the apartment, I'm a pretty private, introspective and quiet person. I generally like to keep to myself and value the space as my place where I can be alone and away from having to interact with the world. Outside, in the "world," I'm a mixed bag - a surefire extrovert, with introvert tendencies from time to time.

My life motto, if you will...the thought I try to keep in mind to keep me centered: the past is done, the future does not exist, the only thing that is REAL, is now.

properties.neighborhood_overview: Chelsea is a neighborhood on the West Side of the borough of Manhattan in New York City. The district's boundaries are roughly 14th Street to the south, 30th Street to the north, the western boundary of the Ladies' Mile Historic District – which lies between the Avenue of the Americas (Sixth Avenue) and Seventh Avenue – to the east, and the Hudson River and West Street to the west. To the north of Chelsea is the neighborhood of Hell's Kitchen, also known as "Clinton," to the northeast is the Garment District, to the east are NoMad and the Flatiron District, to the southwest is the Meatpacking District and to the southeast is the West Village. TODAY- The retail stores of Chelsea reflect the ethnic and social diversity of the area's population. Ethnic restaurants, delis and clothing boutiques are plentiful. properties.neighborhood_overview: Midtown east is only a 10-15 min walk to Central park, Rockefeller center, and 5th Avenue but far enough away from the very touristy areas to give you a taste of what living in New York is like. The neighborhood has some of the best restaurants and bars in New York. One of the best ramen restaurants in NYC and my personal favorite, Totto ramen, is right down the street at 52nd and 2nd. Other neighborhoods are easily accessible through the many subway lines that are only a 5-10 min walk away.
properties.transit: The E, Mar, and 6 train entrance is two blocks away on 53rd and Lexington. The 6 train can take you up and downtown on the east side and can get you directly to places like Grand Central (5 min away) and Wall Street (30 min away). The E and M can take you west to Times Square in 15 minutes. There's a larger subway stop at 59th and Lexington an 8 min walk from the apartment that has the N, Q, R, 4, 5, and 6 subway lines that can get you anywhere else in the city.  The cable car to Roosevelt island is also only 5 blocks way at 59th and 2nd Avenue, and accepts the same cards as the subway and bus system.

The bedroom includes a full-size bed, pull out sofa [full size], small table, closet and dresser. You’ll enjoy access to the Living Area, Kitchen and Bathroom. Enjoy the use of the coffee maker, microwave, stove and fridge [for those delicious To Go meals].  Only steps from a host of trendy restaurants Harlem Public, The Chipped Cup, The Handpulled Noodle, At the Wallace, and Tonalli Cafe Bar.  My place is good for couples, solo adventurers, business travelers, families (with kids).  You’ll appreciate the quiet building with very friendly neighbors.

properties.house_rules: We take pride in our apartment, and ask that you respect and take care of the space. This is our home! You are quite welcome to use the kitchen and fridge, but please clean up after yourselves.  Kindly keep your voices down if coming in late, and please don't smoke or use drugs in the apartment. Children are most welcome!
